Commands of interest:
  Note that all commands are relative to cpsc301-pynx/server/, meaning you must
  be in that directory to execute.

  To install dependencies:
    npm set prefix ~/.node_modules
    echo 'export PATH="$PATH":~/.node_modules/bin' >> ~/.bash_profile
    echo 'export NODE_PATH=~/.node_modules/lib/node_modules:"$NODE_PATH"' >> ~/.bash_profile
    source ~/.bash_profile
    npm install -g sqlite3
    npm install -g mocha

  To set up database:
    bin/create_db # May re-run to overwrite database with virgin copy.

  To run:
    node src/index.js
    curl localhost:8888 # Test to ensure server is running.

  To execute tests:
    # Note: for the tests to work, you must already have the server running.
    mocha

Explanation of files:
  config.js: store configuration options that the sysadmin might want to change.
  index.js: file called on server startup to perform initializations tasks.
  requestHandlers.js: handlers to service requests.
  router.js: routes request to appropriate request handler.
  routes.js: maps URLs to specific handlers.
  server.js: initializes HTTP server and passes requests to router.
  util.js: miscellaneous utility functions of use throughout project.

API docs:
  Node.js:            http://nodejs.org/api/
  Mocha test library: http://visionmedia.github.com/mocha/
  SQLite3 bindings:   https://github.com/developmentseed/node-sqlite3/wiki/API
